The paper proposes a message-passing algorithm for solving the graph isomorphism problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and mathematics. The algorithm is based on the belief-propagation algorithm used in graphical models inference and LDPC decoding. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on graph matching and canonical representations of bipartite graphs, cs.DM and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories.
